Question: The name of the lotion in the right image is two words.

Reference Answer: False

Left image URL: https://lululovelash.files.wordpress.com/2017/09/once-upon-a-time3.png?w=300&h=300

Right image URL: https://ifiwerequeenoftheworld.files.wordpress.com/2017/09/img_1100.png

Program:

```
ANSWER0=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='What is the name of the lotion in the image?')
ANSWER1=EVAL(expr='len({ANSWER0}.split()) == 2')
FINAL_ANSWER=RESULT(var=ANSWER1)
```
Rationale:

<hr><div><b><span style='color: blue;'>ANSWER0</span></b>=<b><span style='color: red;'>VQA</span></b>(<b><span style='color: darkorange;'>image</span></b>=<img style="vertical-align:middle" src="data:image/jpeg;base64,">,&nbsp;<b><span style='color: darkorange;'>question</span></b>='What is the name of the lotion in the image?')=<b><span style='color: green;'>once upon</span></b></div><hr><div><b><span style='color: blue;'>ANSWER1</span></b>=<b><span style='color: red;'>EVAL</span></b>(<b><span style='color: darkorange;'>expression</span></b>="len(ANSWER0.split()) == 2")=<b><span style='color: red;'>EVAL</span></b>(<b><span style='color: darkorange;'>expression</span></b>="len('once upon'.split()) == 2")=<b><span style='color: green;'>True</span></b></div><hr><div><b><span style='color: red;'>RESULT</span></b> -> <b><span style='color: blue;'>ANSWER1</span></b> -> <b><span style='color: green;'>True</span></b></div><hr>

Answer: True
